      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the clothing types, but i'm trying to understand the \"soul\" of it so i don't mess up the branding. when people think of \"urban\" culture, there's usually a specific look associated with certain neighborhoods or groups—like the hip hop aesthetic or certain inner-city vibes. if i'm trying to design for that specific \"street\" demographic, what are the key traits or lifestyles that define their style? like, what are the visual cues that say \"this is authentically from the streets\" vs just being regular casual wear?",
